Hi Bertrand,


I have a doubt, why it can auto add prefix customer/mm/ in every projects during download codes, even though we had not configure it in manifest.
Have we configure something in external gerrit: https://gerrit.legato.io/?


Such as
fetch legato-af from ssh://speng@gerrit.legato.io:29418/customer/mm/legato-af


It will auto change to project customer/mm/legato-afï¼Œ
but we had configured without customer/mm

Customers need to checkout from ssh://gerrit.legato.io:29418/customer/mm/manifest and not ssh://gerrit.legato.io:29418/manifest

Because the remote in the manifest is "..", path to repositories are computed relatively to the manifest path, so there is no need to add any prefix.

Also, here you're modifying an internal manifest, which is converted to an external manifest during the Jenkins publish job. If we had to introduce such change, we would do it at this stage and not on the internal manifest.

Patch Set 1:

That's because only tags that need to be synchronized are pushed to the external gerrit. So if the source manifest mentions 31, the state (external/gerrit-swi/state) will be updated to push the 31 tag.

Because this is a post-generation modification of the manifest, the state would need to be updated manually.
For instance: https://gerrit-legato/#/c/external/gerrit-swi/state/+/27545

commits.commitMessage:
Provide a symlink for releases

This is to maintain compatibility with the documented format.

The manifest has moved from <tag>.xml to <tag>/legato.xml has
to make space for storing other manifests for a particular release.
That's however not the case yet, and the documented format is
still <tag>.xml

Resolves: LE-9971
Change-Id: I1862d4d0f965c7cc787490da16c6329b21e05e4f
commits.subject: Provide a symlink for releases
